        "description": "Currently, anytime either of the Linear/Streaming exposures is null/0, we fail the report, even though it's a valid use case. The ask is to handle this and let the report generate successfully. \n\nRight now it the code is causing a divide-by-0 error. As part of this story, handle all divide by 0 erros for this use case and also any other places where the denominator can be 0.\n\n‌\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- [ ] Reports with empty Linear/Streaming classification should not fail the report. The report should be generated successfully, and no error is thrown back.\n- [ ] All the existing metrics are generated as expected. \n\n| **SOURCECODE** | **DIV0 VULNERABILITY** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `R__get_create_linear_avod_metrics_table.sql` <custom data-type=\"emoji\" data-id=\"id-0\">:white_check_mark:</custom>  | Line 54: `,(total_unique_ids::numeric/'|| p_total_audience_count::varchar ||')*100 AS unique_reach` |\n| `R__get_dim_metrics_sql.sql` | Line 12: Division by (tv_count_per_dim \\* report_days_range) `ROUND(total_hours_spent_per_dim/ (tv_count_per_dim * report_days_range), 2) as average_hours_spent` Line 13: Division by total_hours_spent `(total_hours_spent_per_dim *100/total_hours_spent) as percent_of_hours_spent` Line 14: Division by total_audience_count `(tv_count_per_dim*100/total_audience_count) as percent_of_tvs` |\n| `R__get_cross_channel_usage_tier_desired_metrics_sql.sql` | Lines 78-79, 86-87 `round(cnt * 100.00 / total.total_cnt, 2) unique_reach` `round(total_time_spent / cnt / report_days_range, 2) average_hours_spent_per_day` Lines 96, 105 `round(sum(total_time_missed) / total.total_cnt / report_days_range, 2) average_hours_spent_per_day` |\n| `R__get_ai_cross_channel_avg_time_spent_view_sql.sql` | Lines: 31, 36, 41, 46 `(SUM(total_time_spent)/60.00) / (COUNT(DISTINCT id) * report_days_range) AS avg_time_spent` |\n| `R__get_create_panel_overlap_metrics_sql.sql` | Lines: 118, 131 `ROUND(tv_count / p_app_level_target_count * 100, 2) AS unique_reach` |\n| `R__get_app_type_samsung_apps_metrics_sql.sql` | Lines: 11-13 |\n| `R__report_or_append_linear_to_app_type.sql` | Lines 85-87 (unexposed) `ROUND(total_hours_spent_per_dim/ (tv_count_per_dim * :p_report_days_range), 2) as average_hours_spent` `(total_hours_spent_per_dim *100/total_hours_spent) as percent_of_hours_spent` `(tv_count_per_dim*100/:p_total_unexposed_audience_count) as percent_of_tvs` Lines 110-112 (other) `... /:p_total_other_audience_count ...` Lines 135-137 (universe) `... /:p_total_universe_audience_count ...` |\n| `R__process_sla_metrics.sql` | Lines: 101-103  WHEN delay_minutes <= ALLOWED_DELAY THEN  \n    delay_minutes/ALLOWED_DELAY \\* 30\n\nWHEN delay_minutes BETWEEN ALLOWED_DELAY AND WARNING_DELAY THEN  \n    (delay_minutes - ALLOWED_DELAY) / (WARNING_DELAY - ALLOWED_DELAY) \\* 70\n\nWHEN delay_minutes BETWEEN WARNING_DELAY AND CRITICAL_DELAY THEN  \n    70 + (delay_minutes - WARNING_DELAY) / (CRITICAL_DELAY - WARNING_DELAY) \\* 30 |\n| `R__process_ai_report_metrics.sql` | Line: 306 `,(total_warehouse_credits - total_attributed_credits) / wda.reports_per_day as idle_credits_per_report` |\n| `R__load_snowflake_cost_metrics.sql` | Line: 98 `COUNT(*)::FLOAT / SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER (PARTITION BY allocated_warehouse) AS goal_share` |\n",
