        "description": "### Summary\n\nAdd a \"Presets\" dropdown to the Select Applications modal header bar. This dropdown allows CSMs to browse and select a predefined app bundle instead of manually searching and selecting apps one by one.\n\n![](blob:https://media.staging.atl-paas.net/?type=file&localId=4001ac9c72ae&id=aeb58179-3cad-4be0-83e8-6707a78dd1e4&&collection=&height=733&occurrenceKey=null&width=1167&__contextId=null&__displayType=null&__external=false&__fileMimeType=null&__fileName=null&__fileSize=null&__mediaTraceId=null&url=null)\n‌\n\n### Context\n\n* The dropdown is placed inside the existing Select Applications modal, next to the search/filter field (DR-1)\n* Default value: \"None\" — the modal behaves identically to the current flow when \"None\" is selected (AC-1, AC-2)\n* The dropdown list is populated by calling the backend GET presets endpoint (<custom data-type=\"smartlink\" data-id=\"id-0\">https://adgear.atlassian.net/browse/RSW-1039</custom>), filtered by the country selected in Report Settings (DR-5, AC-3)\n* Only one preset can be selected at a time (DR-2)\n\n### Flow\n\n1. User clicks \"+ Add Apps\" → Select Applications modal opens\n2. Modal renders with \"Presets\" dropdown in header bar, default \"None\"\n3. Call GET presets endpoint with the report's country code\n4. Display preset names in the dropdown list on select open\n5. On preset selection: trigger app auto-population (handled by <custom data-type=\"smartlink\" data-id=\"id-1\">https://adgear.atlassian.net/browse/RSW-1041</custom>)\n\n### Scope\n\n* Add dropdown component to the Select Applications modal header\n* Fetch presets from backend on modal open (or on dropdown expand)\n* Display loading/error states for the fetch\n* When the user re-opens the modal via \"Edit\" button, reflect current state: \"Custom\" (manual or present modified), a preset name (unmodified preset) — AC-10\n* Handle country changes: if user changes country in Report Settings and re-opens modal, the preset list updates accordingly (AC-3)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n* Auto-populating app list and weighting on selection (<custom data-type=\"smartlink\" data-id=\"id-2\">https://adgear.atlassian.net/browse/RSW-1041</custom>)\n* Preset management / editing preset definitions\n* Identify selected present name Custom Group save (after page reload when apps are already selected) - “Custom” state should appear in that case\n\n### Dependencies\n\n* <custom data-type=\"smartlink\" data-id=\"id-3\">https://adgear.atlassian.net/browse/RSW-1039</custom>\n\n### Definition of Done\n\n- [ ] \"Presets\" dropdown visible in the Select Applications modal header, next to search field\n- [ ] Default value is \"None\"\n- [ ] Dropdown populated with presets filtered by selected country\n- [ ] When \"None\" is selected, modal behaves identically to current flow\n- [ ] Dropdown reflects correct state on re-edit (\"None\" / preset name / \"Custom\")\n- [ ] Unit tests for dropdown component rendering and state management\n\n",
        "assignee": {
          "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/477780ca-aefd-44dc-9382-5e69f4091970/rest/api/3/user?accountId=712020%3Ac94e4669-a2fe-440c-ab97-a6f51aa08e32",
