        "description": "## Summary\n\nEnhance the JSON output to support storing results over time so successive runs can be compared, enabling detection of performance regressions.\n\nStorage run results as JSON files is NOT a desirable outcome, we would prefer using a database to persist these results and allow for comparison against previous runs.\n\nLook into automating cost tracking metric collection for jobs that finished 8+ hours ago. This will run on a daily basis and collect these metrics so they can be reviewed later. Using a Snowflake task for this (piggybacking on existing tooling for cost tracking) might be our best bet here.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n* \\[ \\] Results files named with timestamp (e.g., `stress-results-2026-05-07T14-30.json`) \n* \\[ \\] More preferable - store test results in database (such as a Snowflake table)\n* \\[ \\] Add a `compare` Makefile target that reads two result files and prints a diff table\n* \\[ \\] Track key metrics: avg/p50/p95 wall clock time, success rate\n* \\[ \\] Optional: flag regressions (>20% degradation from previous run)\n\n## Estimate\n\nMedium — extends existing output.go with comparison logic\n\n## Dependencies\n\n* RSW-138 (merge stress tool into main)\n\n",
        "assignee": {
          "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/477780ca-aefd-44dc-9382-5e69f4091970/rest/api/3/user?accountId=5fbd5aff4a096400691d80e9",
