        "description": "Description\n\nReplace the current Nova 1 Pro model in the Contextual pipeline with Nova 2 Lite to reduce per-request inference costs while maintaining comparable classification accuracy. This involves adapting the pipeline to work within the lighter model's constraints, including schema adjustments, extended thinking capabilities, improved IAB category matching, and support for raw video input, so the model produces reliable structured outputs without degrading result quality.\n\nAcceptance Criteria\n\n* Nova 2 Lite is fully integrated as the default model in the Contextual pipeline, replacing Nova 1 Pro, with a measurable reduction in per-request cost\n* Classification accuracy with Nova 2 Lite is comparable to the previous Nova 1 Pro setup, supported by a multi-tier category matching strategy (exact, normalized, and fuzzy with length guard) that minimizes false positives and corrects near-miss responses, with null and empty response rates at or below the levels seen with Nova 1 Pro\n* The pipeline supports both composite image and raw video input modes for Nova 2 Lite, with raw video enabled by default to provide richer contextual analysis\n\nDefinition of Done\n\nThis ticket is complete when the Contextual pipeline is running Nova 2 Lite in production with raw video support, per-request costs are confirmed to be lower than the Nova 1 Pro setup, and classification quality meets or exceeds the previous baseline.\n\nDue Date\n\n05/10/2026",
        "assignee": {
          "self": "https://api.atlassian.com/ex/jira/477780ca-aefd-44dc-9382-5e69f4091970/rest/api/3/user?accountId=712020%3A32016ca0-4229-4af5-afb0-55f9e41c5fe8",
